{{Infobox artwork | title = Performing Frogs | image = Performing Frogs, Eugene, Oregon.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = ''Performing Frogs'' at the [[Hult Center for the Performing Arts]] in 2015 | artist = [[David Gilhooly]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1982}} | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = Sculpture | material = {{Flatlist| * Ceramic * concrete }} | subject = Frogs | height_imperial = <!-- (i.e. in imperial units) --> | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = "Treatment urgent" (1993) | city = [[Eugene, Oregon]], United States | museum = | accession = | pushpin_map = USA Oregon Eugene#USA Oregon | coordinates = {{coord|44.052480|-123.093111|display=inline,title}} | owner = | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''''Performing Frogs''''' is a 1982 sculpture by [[David Gilhooly]], located in [[Eugene, Oregon]], in the United States.
==Description== David Gilhooly's ''Performing Frogs'' (1982) is a ceramic sculpture depicting frogs performing acrobatics atop six concrete pillars; some of them have birds sitting on their heads. It is installed at the [[Hult Center for the Performing Arts]]. A nearby plaque reads: {{Small|PERFORMING FROGS / DAVID GILHOOLY / 1982}}. The sculpture's condition was deemed "treatment urgent" by the [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]" program in October 1993. It was administered by the City of Eugene then.<ref name=SI>{{cite web|title=Performing Frogs, (sculpture).|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!328725~!0#focus|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=October 2, 2015}}</ref>
