{{for|the Canadian comedian with a similar name|Phil Nichol}} '''Philip Nicol''' (born 1953, [[Caerphilly]], [[Wales]])<ref name="Moore 60">{{Citation |author=David Moore |title=A Taste of the Avant Garde: 56 Group Wales 56 Years |publisher=Crooked Window |place=[[Brecon]] |year=2012 |page=60 |format=Book |isbn=978-0-9563602-1-2 }}</ref> is a Welsh painter.
Nicol graduated from [[Cardiff School of Art and Design|Cardiff College of Art]]. He has been a lecturer at the Cardiff School and at [[Limerick School of Art and Design|Limerick Art College]], [[Éire]].<ref name="Moore 60" />
His paintings often portray twilight inner city landscapes.
He was winner of the Gold Medal for Fine Art at the [[National Eisteddfod of Wales]] in 2001.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gold Medal for Fine Art |work=Eisteddfod.org.uk |publisher=The National Eisteddfod of Wales |url=http://www.eisteddfod.org.uk/english/about-us/our-history/winners/gold-medal-for-fine-art/ |format= |accessdate=8 January 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226073553/http://www.eisteddfod.org.uk/english/about-us/our-history/winners/gold-medal-for-fine-art/ |archivedate=26 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>
Nicol was a member of the [[56 Group Wales]] from 1984 to 1991. He is exhibition director at the [[BayArt]] gallery, [[Cardiff Bay]].<ref name="Moore 60" /><ref>{{cite news|author=Moira Sharkey |title=you BUTE-Y! |work=[[South Wales Echo]] |publisher= |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/you+BUTE-Y!-a083237656 |date=23 February 2002 |accessdate=8 January 2014}}</ref>
His paintings are in the public collections of the [[National Museum of Wales Cardiff|National Museum of Wales]], [[Newport Art Gallery]] and the [[National Assembly for Wales]].<ref name=Yourpaintings>{{cite web|title=Philip Nicol paintings |work=BBC Your Paintings |publisher=[[BBC]] |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/arts/yourpaintings/artists/nicol-philip-b-1953/paintings/slideshow#/0 |format=Slideshow |accessdate=8 January 2014}}</ref>
